  "tells": [
    "Common mistake: Overcommitting to a single legendary without answers, leaving you vulnerable to removal or board wipes.",
    "Unique interaction: Kaalia's ETB puts the creature onto the battlefield tapped and attacking, which can trigger 'when this creature attacks' effects immediately.",
    "Also, you can chain multiple legendaries in one turn if you have enough mana and targets, creating a snowball effect that's hard to answer.",
    "Always keep a legendary creature in hand when you cast Kaalia to maximize value."
  ],
  "predicted_lines": [
    {
      "trigger": "early game",
      "line": "Turn 1: Play a land, cast Sol Ring/Arcane Signet, or play a cheap mana-producing land."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "early game",
      "line": "Turn 2: Cast Kaalia if you have 3 mana, or continue ramping."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "early game",
      "line": "If you have a legendary creature in hand, cast Kaalia, let it resolve, and use its ETB to put the legendary onto the battlefield tapped and attacking to apply immediate pressure or trigger ETB/attack abilities."
    }
  ],
